Glass-field thermal anomaly investigation
-1 1 3 0 65 78 3340 5500 5 2400000 0
5764 5765 5766
A Glasswalk Guide family has reported freshly fused glass in a section of the Belt that has been stable for generations, and the Kiess route-dispatch office is treating the anomaly as a threat to certified Reach transit lanes. Thermal fault elementals have taken up residence at the fault ridge, vitrified sand horrors have formed from the fused material, and molten glass sentinels are preventing investigation of the anomaly zone. Eliminate one of each so the Guide elder can advise on route adjustment.
The thermal anomaly investigation is complete and the source creatures have been eliminated. The Kiess postmaster has forwarded the Guide elder's assessment confirming a previously dormant fault has reactivated, likely due to Ninth Meridian geological drift, to the Scorched Wastes survey network for cross-reference. Mandatory route adjustments for all Kiess-certified caravan contracts through the affected Belt section are now in effect.

